'''''The Long Walk Home''''' was a 1990 film starring [[Sissy Spacek]] and [[Whoopi Goldberg]].  The film was set in [[Montgomery, Alabama]] during the 1955 [[Montgomery bus boycott]], and featured Goldberg as a young African-American maid, employed by a young white woman, played by Spacek.  When Goldberg's character decides to honor the bus boycott, opting to walk several miles to and from her employer's home, her employer decides to offer her a ride, thus thrusting both women into the politically charged situation.

